## DNS — Bind9

### Instalación

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y bind9 bind9utils bind9-doc
```

### Configuración de zonas

En `/etc/bind/named.conf.local` se han definido dos zonas: la zona directa para `novatech.cat` y la zona inversa para `10.40.0.0/24`:

```
zone "novatech.cat" {
    type master;
    file "/etc/bind/zones/db.novatech.cat";
};

zone "40.10.in-addr.arpa" {
    type master;
    file "/etc/bind/zones/db.10.40";
};
```

### Zona directa — db.novatech.cat

```
$TTL    604800
@       IN      SOA     ns1.novatech.cat. admin.novatech.cat. (
                              2         ; Serial
                         604800         ; Refresh
                          86400         ; Retry
                        2419200         ; Expire
                         604800 )       ; Negative Cache TTL

@       IN      NS      ns1.novatech.cat.

ns1     IN      A       10.40.0.10
mail    IN      A       10.40.0.10
www     IN      A       172.16.0.20

@       IN      MX      10      mail.novatech.cat.
```

### Zona inversa — db.10.40

```
$TTL    604800
@       IN      SOA     ns1.novatech.cat. admin.novatech.cat. (
                              1         ; Serial
                         604800         ; Refresh
                          86400         ; Retry
                        2419200         ; Expire
                         604800 )       ; Negative Cache TTL

@       IN      NS      ns1.novatech.cat.

10      IN      PTR     ns1.novatech.cat.
10      IN      PTR     mail.novatech.cat.
20      IN      PTR     siem.novatech.cat.
```

